---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy - Your Data Security | QR Barcode Tools";
const description =
    "Read our comprehensive Privacy Policy. We guarantee 100% client-side rendering. Your QR and barcode inputs never touch our servers.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <div
            class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/80 p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm space-y-6 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm md:text-base"
        >
            <h1
                class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 border-b border-slate-100 pb-4"
            >
                Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Last updated: June 17, 2026</p>

            <p>
                At <strong>QR Barcode Tools</strong>, accessible from our
                domain, one of our main priorities is the privacy of our
                visitors. This Privacy Policy document outlines our strict
                policies regarding your input data and general analytics
                collection.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                1. Local Processing Guarantee (Zero Uploads)
            </h2>
            <p>
                We do not employ any backend application servers, databases, or
                cloud storage systems to record your tool inputs. When you
                generate a QR code (including WiFi passwords, website links, or
                contact vCards) or barcodes (including Code 128 or EAN-13), the
                entire processing is executed <strong
                    >locally inside your web browser</strong
                >:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
                <li>
                    Your network keys or text values are never sent over the
                    Internet.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Your contact vCard details are translated into QR dots
                    locally using open-source client-side code.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Your downloaded files (PNG/SVG) are compiled on your device.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                2. Traffic Analytics & Cookies
            </h2>
            <p>
                To monitor overall website performance and optimize user
                navigation, we may utilize standard lightweight analytical
                scripts (such as Cloudflare Web Analytics or Google Analytics).
                These scripts do not track personal identification info. They
                only measure:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4 space-y-1">
                <li>
                    Browser type and general geographic region (country level).
                </li>
                <li>Pages viewed and total session length.</li>
                <li>Standard referrer domains.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                These analytics help us understand which tools are popular so we
                can refine and improve our page loading speeds.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                3. No Sale of Personal Data
            </h2>
            <p>
                Since we do not collect, store, or sell any personal data,
                emails, or passwords, we have nothing to sell to data brokers or
                advertising campaigns. We are 100% compliant with general data
                protection regulations (such as GDPR and CCPA) by default due to
                our client-side architectural design.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 pt-4">
                4. Third-Party Links
            </h2>
            <p>
                Our website may contain articles with outbound links to
                informative guides or external resources. We are not responsible
                for the privacy practices of external domains. We encourage you
                to read the privacy statements of any third-party websites you
                visit.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
